INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '6d1835f9-0bd7-4894-9e02-c334a5dcb88d',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$ethers_js Wallet Connection — BrowserProvider, WalletConnect, and Signer Abstraction$escape$,
  $escape$ethers.js v6 unifies wallet connections through `BrowserProvider`, which wraps any EIP-1193-compatible provider — MetaMask, Coinbase Wallet, or WalletConnect's `UniversalProvider`. The key insight: every wallet ultimately yields an `AbstractSigner`, so your app logic stays wallet-agnostic once you have one.

For MetaMask and Coinbase Wallet (injected), wrap `window.ethereum` directly: `new ethers.BrowserProvider(window.ethereum)`. For WalletConnect v2, initialize `UniversalProvider` from `@walletconnect/universal-provider`, then pass it to `BrowserProvider` identically — the interface is the same.

Call `provider.getSigner()` to get an `ethers.JsonRpcSigner`, which exposes `.sendTransaction()`, `.signMessage()`, and `.signTypedData()` uniformly. Avoid storing the provider long-term — re-request the signer per session to handle account changes. Listen to `provider.on('accountsChanged', ...)` and `provider.on('chainChanged', ...)` via the raw `window.ethereum` handle, since `BrowserProvider` doesn't re-emit these. This pattern lets you swap wallets — MetaMask today, WalletConnect tomorrow — without touching transaction logic.$escape$,
  $escape$import { ethers } from 'ethers';
import { UniversalProvider } from '@walletconnect/universal-provider';

// MetaMask / Coinbase Wallet (injected EIP-1193)
const injectedProvider = new ethers.BrowserProvider(window.ethereum);
const injectedSigner = await injectedProvider.getSigner();

// WalletConnect v2
const wcProvider = await UniversalProvider.init({
  projectId: 'YOUR_PROJECT_ID',
  metadata: { name: 'ByteAI', description: '', url: '', icons: [] },
});
await wcProvider.connect({ namespaces: { eip155: { methods: ['eth_sendTransaction', 'personal_sign'], chains: ['eip155:1'], events: ['accountsChanged'] } } });

const wcEthersProvider = new ethers.BrowserProvider(wcProvider);
const wcSigner = await wcEthersProvider.getSigner();

// Both signers share the same interface
console.log(await injectedSigner.getAddress());
console.log(await wcSigner.getAddress());$escape$,
